But I also know she would probably drive back up here when she's having fun down there. Or feel guilty about going down to visit his gf, which is the last thing I want. So hello Twitter, here are my brain words

Thank you internet, for providing me a blank page to word vomit... if someone is actually reading this, um. Why? Also, don't worry, I'm fine. I'll make it. I'm just feeling bad today. And feel guilty for feeling bad. Bri is out of town and I want to like talk to him,

Which, of course, makes me feel worse... I feel shitty on many levels, and I know Bri wants what's best for me and supports me, but even the thought of them being disappointed in me literally brings me to tears and makes me feel so much worse still...

I keep feeling so bad about forgetting, about the phone calls, about my group, about that paper, about my T Shot, but that doesn't stop me! Or start me, I guess I should say. It makes me feel bad to the point that I literally don't tell Bri about it most of the time
It's literally over $100 for four weeks. And that's a low ball. I think it's more towards $160... maybe Medicaid will help me afford it? Hopefully

Since I was forced back to the regular shot from an epi-pen like device, it's become SO hard to remember and do. There was an insurance mix up, so I could afford it for like a year before they billed me the correct amount. Even with insurance and a coupon from the manufacturer,

I'm so happy to be transitioning but goddammit stabbing myself is hard to find the energy for,, I keep forgetting and remembering when I'm not home, like rn. I'm at work. I should've done this shot on Sunday. Last Sunday. This isn't the first time it's late
that I didn't know existed and was due the first Friday this month, I think? But I didn't know about it. Until after it was due. And I haven't. Um. Started it.

In my only other class, my capstone, I also feel woefully behind. Because I am. I have a survey that has to pass scrutiny before I put it out there, and I have to edit it. I haven't touched it for two weeks. There's a paper, an easy one, I think it's a game plan

I once literally got a 102% or something on a test and was confused on how someone got 108%. Any grade, even if it's more than perfect, feels like a failure because I can always do better. So I do not check my grades...

I'm part of a group in my stats course, and I feel totally useless because I'm busy af and never feel like I'm pulling my weight. My prof in that class gives feedback on assignments, which is great, but it requires me to check my grades...
And I was overwhelmed because college in person sucks absolute ass and is 1000% more draining. I was over it before it even started last semester...

I haven't even dialed the number yet... and since I literally don't have health insurance (I need to choose a plan. That's it.), I haven't made appointments with my doctors. I haven't seen any of my docs since maybe October? Because I knew my insurance was running out.

Like yes, I do suck at this adulting thing! I've been trying to get myself to contact Medicaid for. Literal months at this point. I finally had all the info I needed, but the one piece of paper I need rn is gone! So I have to call. I've been trying to for over a week.

My therapist was proud last week that I can recognize when my brain is being dumb and overdramatic, but it's still hard to like. Ignore it. Especially when I don't think the alarmingly Karen-like voice in my head is wrong about me...

Okay end random 7 am rant lol

And you'll find that partner someday if you want one (or more!), your body is lovable and beautiful/handsome! Trans folks are not doomed to loneliness! We deserve happiness just as much as cis people!

Wanting to "blend in" is absolutely valid, even if it isn't for safety reasons! You deserve to exist in your body as you, and change it as you see fit to match who you are! You deserve happiness, supportive friends and family (found family is just as valid)

And I hope someone in the void I'm typing to gets some inspiration, or feels a little safer, or even just smiles a bit. Because being trans? It has it's bad parts, it's great! I wouldn't change it for being cis! I'm aware of so much more in the world because of being trans

And I think I'm going to make that my goal, y'know? I'm out at work, but some people literally don't know that. I'm not good at defending myself, so I've been quiet when people misgender me. But I think my weird rant has inspired mebto so better lol

I hope I can use my visibility, my pride in who I am, to normalize trans bodies. Even if that's to like two people at work, or to someone in my family that just doesn't "get it," every person educated counts. Every person educated could save a life in the long run

I'm aware of my privilege as a trans person, I literally am a white androgynous non-binary person. When someone thinks of a trans-masc person, they think of someone who looks like me. And I hope I'm using my privilege for good, to help out my trans siblings with less privilege
I'm proud to be trans, just like I'm proud to be queer! I think that no matter how I was born, I would still be trans, just like I would still be queer!
There's absolutely nothing wrong with wanting/needing to blend in with the cis population (or perceived cis); I think it's sad that it's almost become an expectation, both from cis and trans people
And of course queer people still do face dangers worldwide, I'm not at all belittling that. It's just been an interesting change

For some folks, being seen as trans could literally be a death sentence. Cis people REALLY don't like when we say "hey we don't fit your gender categories" or "hey, you think I was j gender, turns out I'm k!"
Like for the most part, queer people are like "oh god FORBID someone thinks I'm straight haha" and that's not the case as much with trans folks
You know, the most stark difference between when I came out as queer vs when I came out as trans is the amount of pride people have in their labels, y'know?
